- VSCode Version: Version 1.3.1 (1.3.1) e6b4afa53e9c0f54edef1673de9001e9f0f547ae
- OS Version: OSX 10.11.6 (15G31)

I am trying to write an extension for VS Code where I need to insert text in two different places of the current document (module importing and injection).

What happens it is that if I edit the text as:

```
window.activeTextEditor.edit(editBuilder => {
    var indexA = new Position(0,0)
    var indexB = new Position(1,0)
    editBuilder.insert(indexA, 'Insert A')
    editBuilder.insert(indexB, 'Insert B')
})
```

it will work just fine, however, if I split it into two different calls:

```
window.activeTextEditor.edit(editBuilder => {           
   var indexA = new Position(0,0)
   editBuilder.insert(indexA, 'Insert A')
})

window.activeTextEditor.edit(editBuilder => {
    var indexB = new Position(1,0);
    editBuilder.insert(indexB, 'Insert B')
})
```

Only the first one will be in the document.
